Introduction

Do-A, formerly known as Bella, is a South Korean singer and rapper. She was the main rapper of the girl group ALICE. On April 11, 2022, ELRIS was rebranded to ALICE, and Bella changed her stage name to Do-A.

On May 2, 2024, her contract with IOK Company had expired, and she announced the next day that she would be leaving ALICE.
